parameters: A burnt out campfire lies here, along with a few empty bottles of booze. You can't say for certain who was drinking these, but it looks like they dropped a few peices of silver while they were at it, which you quickly collect.
<wrap> A burnt out campfire lies here, with a few discarded booze bottles. Nobody's returned to toss a few coins around though, so there's not much of interest here any longer.

You head down the path in the forest and find yourself in a rather dense patch of trees. You are distracted by a rustling sound to your left, which ends up just being a small squirrel popping out of the brush. Unfortunately, the Lizardman hiding in the bush to your \firight\fi finds this to be an ideal distraction as he pops out and ambushes you.

Despite the disadvantage of being ambushed, you still managed to blast the Lizardman into submission. You probably won’t get very far walking into ambushes like this all the time though, might be best to be a little more careful from now on, unless you \fiwant\fi a Lizardman to ravish your helpless body, of course. Now, what should you take to prove you’ve completed this quest?

You could take the sword, but it's pretty much the most generic looking thing you've ever seen, so there's no reason to assume it actually came from a lizardman. The loincloth then? You don't really want to have to touch it, but it will probably, er, smell? Smell like a Lizardman, that is.
You don't see a better option, so you quickly cut the side of the Lizardman's loincloth and snatch it away from him.
Woah there, if that's what you wanted to begin with, why didn't you just say so? I'm always willing to pump a load into a cutie like yourself, so why don't you climb aboard?

You see the Lizardman's cock rapidly stiffening, as he seems to think you're trying to have sex with him. You're going to have to disappoint him though, as you've already got what you wanted out of this encounter. Just looking at the size of that thing makes you cringe, how could that fit inside another person?
Actually, you realize you know ''exactly'' how that could fit inside someone, and feel your cheeks start to flush at the memory.

You shake your head to clear your thoughts, you could probably head back to Elmgar now, or explore the area a bit more. Perhaps you can make a bit of coin off these Lizardmen, though the coin pouch you found is rather light.

You head around the main path, obviously not walking down the route known for its ambushes, and spot a peculiar sight. There appears to be the tail of a lizardman sticking out of that bush, how curious. It appears you’ve stumbled upon an ambush site, and you’ve been lucky enough to do it unnoticed. Trying to skirt past him completely might be a bit risky though, all he would have to do is turn around to spot you. Might as well take this opportunity to get the jump on him.

You enter the forest in search of a Lizardman, deciding to stick near the paths formed by constant travel through the area. Lizardmen are known to ambush travelers and liberate them of some of their goods, and, if they are in the mood, having a bit of... \fifun\fi with them, as well. Lizardmen are generally pretty weak, so defeating one shouldn’t be too hard. You just hope you can stick to taking them on one by one.
